<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-17T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="705" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d705">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/840: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-17T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 17,
                                            1919, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>For the Minister only—to be deciphered by him.</p>
                            <p>Were you present at a recent meeting of a so-called British-American
                                Association which passed a resolution in reference to the Shantung
                                settlement? Please answer by cable, indicating whether the British
                                Minister was present.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>